ns%20for%20her%20children%20and%20the%20country's%20%26quot%3Bpsychedelic%20sunsets%26quot%3B%2C%20she%20said%20in%20a%20rare%20public%20letter%20marking%20three%20years%20since%20her%20mysterious%20arrest%20in%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECheng%20describes%20her%20bleak%20prison%20conditions%20in%20a%20candid%20note%20dictated%20to%20Australian%20officials%20from%20her%20cell%2C%20casting%20new%20light%20on%20a%20long-running%20point%20of%20friction%20between%20Canberra%20and%20Beijing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20miss%20the%20sun%2C%26quot%3B%20reads%20the%20message%2C%20described%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Blove%20letter%26quot%3B%20to%20Australia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20my%20cell%2C%20the%20sunlight%20shines%20through%20the%20window%20but%20I%20can%20stand%20in%20it%20for%20only%2010%20hours%20a%20year.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20former%20anchor%20for%20Chinese%20state%20broadcaster%20CGTN%20was%20arrested%20in%202020%2C%20and%20has%20been%20formally%20charged%20with%20%26quot%3Bsupplying%20state%20secrets%20overseas%26quot%3B%20--%20though%20no%20further%20details%20have%20been%20supplied.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHer%20message%20was%20shared%20with%20Australian%20news%20outlets%20and%20on%20the%20social%20media%20platform%20X%20by%20Cheng's%20partner%2C%20Nick%20Coyle%2C%20on%20Thursday%20evening.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECheng%20was%20detained%20at%20a%20time%20of%20rising%20tensions%20between%20China%20and%20Australia%2C%20with%20some%20questioning%20whether%20political%20manoeuvring%20played%20a%20part%20in%20her%20arrest.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHer%20case%20is%20often%20compared%20with%20that%20of%20Chinese-born%20Australian%20writer%20Yang%20Jun%2C%20who%20has%20been%20detained%20in%20China%20since%202019%20on%20vaguely%20defined%20espionage%20charges.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlthough%20the%20relationship%20between%20Canberra%20and%20Beijing%20has%20warmed%20in%20recent%20months%20--%20with%20China%20dismantling%20a%20series%20of%20hefty%20trade%20tariffs%20--%20Cheng's%20imprisonment%20remains%20a%20point%20of%20stress%20in%20the%20relationship.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAustralian%20Foreign%20Minister%20Penny%20Wong%20said%20the%20entire%20country%20wanted%20to%20see%20Cheng%20%26quot%3Breunited%20with%20her%20children%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAustralia%20has%20consistently%20advocated%20for%20Ms%20Cheng%2C%20and%20asked%20that%20basic%20standards%20of%20justice%2C%20procedural%20fairness%20and%20humane%20treatment%20to%20be%20met%20in%20accordance%20with%20international%20norms%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%20Friday%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20will%20continue%20to%20support%20Ms%20Cheng%20and%20her%20family%20and%20to%20advocate%20for%20Ms%20Cheng's%20interests%20and%20wellbeing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20Coyle%20said%20he%20had%20serious%20concerns%20about%20a%20%26quot%3Brange%20of%20health%20issues%26quot%3B%20Cheng%20faced%20behind%20bars.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Miss%20my%20children'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20poignant%20message%2C%20the%20mother%20of%20two%20said%20she%20had%20not%20seen%20a%20tree%20in%20three%20years%20and%20spoke%20of%20her%20longing%20for%20Australia's%20bushwalks%2C%20beaches%20and%20%26quot%3Bpsychedelic%20sunsets%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20her%20bedding%20in%20jail%20was%20only%20taken%20out%20to%20air%20once%20a%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20the%20Chinese%20in%20me%20that%20has%20probably%20gone%20beyond%20the%20legal%20limits%20of%20sentimentality%2C%26quot%3B%20writes%20Cheng%2C%20who%20describes%20herself%20as%20Chinese-Australian.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMost%20of%20all%20I%20miss%20my%20children%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20ends%20the%20letter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECheng%20has%20been%20detained%20since%20August%202020%2C%20but%20was%20only%20formally%20arrested%20in%20February%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20was%20tried%20last%20March%20behind%20closed%20doors%2C%20with%20even%20Australia's%20ambassador%20to%20China%20blocked%20from%20entering%20the%20court%20to%20observe%20proceedings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20deferred%20the%20verdict%20and%20Cheng's%20sentence%2C%20which%20could%20extend%20to%20life%20in%20prison.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BShe%20has%20missed%20her%20daughter%20going%20to%20high%20school.%20Her%20parents%20aren't%20getting%20any%20younger%20and%20Lei%20is%20their%20only%20child.%20So%20time%20is%20getting%20more%20and%20more%20precious%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Sydney%20Morning%20Herald%20quoted%20Coyle%20as%20saying%20on%20Thursday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWong%20raised%20Cheng's%20case%20when%20she%20met%20China's%20top%20diplomat%20Wang%20Yi%20on%20the%20sidelines%20of%20an%20ASEAN%20summit%20in%20Jakarta%20last%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691724600000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-08%2Fgptshbng_cheng-lei-_625x300_11_August_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fi-miss-the-sun-australian-journalist-cheng-lei-jailed-in-china-4288462%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Jailed%20Australian%20journalist%20Cheng%20Lei%20yearns%20for%20her%20children%20and%20the%20country's%20%26quot%3Bpsychedelic%20sunsets%26quot%3B%2C%20she%20said%20in%20a%20rare%20public%20letter%20marking%20three%20years%20since%20her%20mysterious%20arrest%20in%20China.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fi-miss-the-sun-australian-journalist-cheng-lei-jailed-in-china-4288462%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fi-miss-the-sun-australian-journalist-cheng-lei-jailed-in-china-4288462%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndt