20since%20the%20coup.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20reason%20for%20including%20him%20is%20stated%20in%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feur-lex.europa.eu%2Flegal-content%2FEN%2FTXT%2FPDF%2F%3Furi%3DOJ%3AL%3A2023%3A183I%3AFULL%5C%22%3EOfficial%20Journal%20of%20the%20European%20Union.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20his%20capacity%20as%20Union%20minister%2C%20he%20carries%20out%20duties%20in%20support%20of%20the%20military%20regime%E2%80%99s%20repressive%20immigration%20and%20population%20policy%20such%20as%20restrictions%20for%20citizens%20to%20travel%20within%20the%20country%20as%20well%20as%20the%20policy%20of%20the%20regime%20towards%20the%20minority%20of%20the%20Rohingya%20in%20violation%20of%20human%20rights.%20As%20Minister%20for%20Immigration%20and%20Population%2C%20he%20also%20participates%20in%20preparations%20for%20the%20elections%20announced%20by%20the%20military%20in%20order%20to%20legitimise%20the%20illegal%20coup%20of%20February%202021.%20Myint%20Kyaing%20is%2C%20therefore%2C%20responsible%20for%20undermining%20democracy%20and%20the%20rule%20of%20law%20in%20Myanmar%2FBurma%20and%20for%20providing%20support%20for%20actions%20that%20threaten%20the%20peace%2C%20security%20and%20stability%20in%20Myanmar%2FBurma.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENews%20outlets%20in%20Myanmar%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gnlm.com.mm%2Fmyanmar-delegation-seeks-information-on-aadhaar-mosip-systems-in-india%2F%5C%22%3Ereported%20Myint%20Kyaing%E2%80%99s%20July%2028%20visit%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20Unique%20Identification%20Authority%20of%20India%20(UIDAI)%20Technology%20Centre%20in%20Bengaluru%2C%20where%20officials%20briefed%20him%20on%20the%20system.%20He%20also%20visited%20the%20International%20Institute%20of%20Information%20Technology%20(IIIT)%20in%20the%20city%2C%20and%20flew%20back%20to%20Yangon%20via%20Chennai.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMyint%20Kyaing%20also%20visited%20the%20regional%20office%20of%20the%20Aadhaar%20Centre%20in%20New%20Delhi.%20During%20his%20visit%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mdn.gov.mm%2Fen%2Fmoip-union-minister-observes-aadhaar-number-issuance-process-new-delhi%5C%22%3Eofficials%20in%20charge%20of%20the%20Aadhaar%20system%20briefed%20the%20visiting%20minister%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0Myanmar%E2%80%99s%20contentious%20and%20exclusionary%20citizenship%20laws%20based%20on%20race%20and%20ethnicity%20make%20any%20system%20of%20identity%20in%20that%20country%20a%20fraught%20issue.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20not%20known%20if%20the%20Myanmar%20minister%20met%20any%20Indian%20leaders%20or%20officials.%20A%20Myanmar%20Ministry%20of%20Information%20statement%20dated%20July%2027%20said%20Myint%20Kyaing%E2%80%99s%20visit%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.moi.gov.mm%2Fmoi%3Aeng%2Fnews%2F11119%5C%22%3Eon%20an%20invitation%20%E2%80%9Cfrom%20the%20Indian%20government%3Cstrong%3E.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs%20(MEA)%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20queries%20about%20the%20visit%2C%20and%20there%20was%20no%20coverage%20of%20it%20in%20the%20Indian%20media%20organisations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Findia-doesnt-follow-national-sanctions-jaishankar-on-myanmar-at-quad-meet%2Farticleshow%2F89512815.cms%5C%22%3Edoes%20not%20recognise%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20sanctions%20imposed%20by%20western%20countries%20on%20Myanmar%20officials%2C%20and%20has%20steadily%20increased%20contact%20with%20the%20regime%20in%20Nay%20Pyi%20Taw%20in%20the%20three%20years%20since%20the%20coup.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20November%202021%2C%20then%20foreign%20secretary%20Harsh%20Shringla%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fmyanmar-first-visit-harsh-shringla-coup-manipur-democracy%5C%22%3Ewas%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20first%20high%20ranking%20official%20to%20visit%20Myanmar%20after%20the%20coup.%20After%20a%20year%2C%20foreign%20secretary%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fforeign-secretary-meets-myanmar-military-leaders-discusses-border-management%2Farticle66170089.ece%5C%22%3EVinay%20Kwatra%E2%80%99s%20visit%3C%2Fa%3E%20indicated%20that%20India%20was%20prepared%20to%20downplay%20its%20stated%20commitment%20for%20the%20return%20to%20democracy%20in%20Myanmar.%20He%20discussed%20border%20management%20issues%2C%20and%20infrastructure%20projects.%20Human%20trafficking%20was%20also%20on%20the%20agenda%20as%20several%20Indians%20from%20Tamil%20Nadu%20were%20lured%20with%20promises%20of%20IT%20jobs%2C%20but%20found%20themselves%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Findia-news%2F13-indians-trapped-in-fake-it-job-racket-rescued-from-myanmar-reach-tamil-nadu-101664964277636.html%5C%22%3Escamming%20operation%3C%2Fa%3E%20located%20in%20a%20remote%20area%20on%20the%20Thai-Myanmar%20border.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20unlike%20the%20previous%20year%2C%20when%20Shringla%20met%20with%20members%20of%20the%20overthrown%20National%20League%20for%20Democracy%2C%20Kwatra%20did%20not%20ask%20to%20meet%20any%20democratic%20leaders.%20The%20MEA%20spokesperson%E2%80%99s%20tweet%20mentioned%20Myanmar%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Cdemocratic%20transition%E2%80%9D%20but%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fthehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fforeign-secretary-meets-myanmar-military-leaders-discusses-border-management%2Farticle66170089.ece%5C%22%3Ethe%20official%20MEA%20press%20release%20%3C%2Fa%3Emade%20no%20mention%20of%20any%20discussion%20on%20the%20restoration%20of%20democracy%2C%20or%20the%20release%20of%20those%20detained.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20year%20has%20seen%20the%20two%20countries%20engage%20at%20high%20political%20levels.%20On%20July%2016%2C%20external%20affairs%20minister%20S.%20Jaishankar%20met%20with%20the%20new%20Myanmar%20foreign%20minister%20Than%20Swe%20on%20the%20sidelines%20of%20the%20Mekong%20Ganga%20Cooperation%20Mechanism%20meeting%20in%20Bangkok.%20They%20appear%20to%20have%20discussed%20the%20violence%20in%20Manipur.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CUnderlined%20the%20importance%20of%20ensuring%20peace%20and%20stability%20in%20our%20border%20areas.%20These%20have%20been%20seriously%20disturbed%20recently%20and%20any%20actions%20that%20aggravate%20the%20situation%20should%20be%20avoided.%20Flagged%20concerns%20about%20human%20and%20drug%20trafficking.%20Urged%20stronger%20cooperation%20among%20relevant%20parties%20for%20the%20early%20return%20of%20trafficked%20victims%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FDrSJaishankar%2Fstatus%2F1680434567633838080%5C%22%3EJaishankar%20said%20in%20a%20tweet%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0after%20the%20meeting.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EMet%20H.E.%20U%20Than%20Swe%20on%20the%20sidelines%20of%20the%20Mekong%20Ganga%20Cooperation%20(MGC)%20meeting%20in%20Bangkok%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOur%20discussions%20focused%20on%20connectivity%20initiatives%20that%20have%20a%20larger%20regional%20significance.%20These%20will%20also%20be%20discussed%20at%20the%20MGC%20meeting%20this%20afternoon.%20Stressed%20the%E2%80%A6%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FvaOoa0RAFL%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2FvaOoa0RAFL%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%94%20Dr.%20S.%20Jaishankar%20(%40DrSJaishankar)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FDrSJaishankar%2Fstatus%2F1680434567633838080%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EJuly%2016%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETwo%20weeks%20earlier%2C%20on%20June%2030%2C%20defence%20secretary%20Giridhar%20Aramane%20visited%20Nay%20Pyi%20Taw.%20An%20official%20release%20said%20he%20met%20the%20junta%20chief%20Senior%20General%20Min%20Aung%20Hlaing%20in%20Nay%20Pyi%20Taw%2C%20and%20the%20Defence%20Minister%20of%20Myanmar%20Gen%20(Retd.)%20Mya%20Tun%20Oo%20.%20He%20also%20held%20meetings%20with%20Commander-in-Chief%2C%20Myanmar%20Navy%20Admiral%20Moe%20Aung%2C%20and%20Chief%20of%20Defence%20Industries%20Lt%20Gen%20Khan%20Myint%20Than.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20visit%20provided%20an%20opportunity%20to%20raise%20matters%20relating%20to%20India%E2%80%99s%20security%20with%20the%20senior%20leadership%20of%20Myanmar.%20During%20the%20meetings%2C%20the%20two%20sides%20discussed%20issues%20related%20to%20maintenance%20of%20tranquillity%20in%20the%20border%20areas%2C%20illegal%20trans-border%20movements%20and%20transnational%20crimes%20such%20as%20drug%20trafficking%20and%20smuggling.%20Both%20sides%20reaffirmed%20their%20commitment%20to%20ensure%20that%20their%20respective%20territories%20would%20not%20be%20allowed%20to%20be%20used%20for%20any%20activities%20inimical%20to%20the%20other%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpib.gov.in%2FPressReleaseIframePage.aspx%3FPRID%3D1936668%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20a%20statement%20from%20PIB.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fhow-india-is-supporting-myanmars-military-with-arms%2Fa-65733102%5C%22%3EUN%20report%20in%20May%20revealed%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20since%20the%202021%20coup%2C%2022%20India-based%20suppliers%2C%20including%20state-owned%20entities%2C%20sent%20%2451%20million%20in%20arms%2C%20raw%20material%20and%20other%20military%20supplies%20to%20the%20junta.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20May%2C%20Union%20minister%20for%20ports%2C%20shipping%20and%20waterways%2C%20Sarbananda%20Sonowal%2C%20attended%20the%20opening%20of%20Sittwe%20Port%20built%20by%20the%20Indian%20company%20Essar%20as%20part%20of%20the%20Kaladan%20Multi-Modal%20Transit%20Transport%20Project.%20The%20project%20hopes%20to%20improve%20connectivity%20between%20the%20Indian%20mainland%20and%20the%20North%20East%20through%20Myanmar.%20Sittwe%20Port%20is%20one%20part.%20The%20other%20part%20of%20the%20project%20is%20to%20connect%20the%20port%20to%20Myanmar%E2%80%99s%20border%20with%20Mizoram%20at%20Paletwa%20via%20the%20Kaladan%20river%2C%20but%20this%20is%20proving%20difficult%20due%20to%20the%20ongoing%20conflict%20in%20Myanmar%E2%80%99s%20Rakhine%20and%20Chin%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20April%2C%20the%20Indian%20Council%20of%20World%20Affairs%2C%20a%20think%20tank%20funded%20by%20the%20Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs%2C%20hosted%20a%20Thailand-initiated%20track%201.5%20dialogue%20%E2%80%93%20others%20at%20the%20dialogue%20were%20Myanmar%E2%80%99s%20neighbours%20Bangladesh%20and%20China%2C%20and%20non-maritime%20ASEAN%20members%20Laos%20and%20Cambodia%20%E2%80%93%20to%20brainstorm%20over%20how%20to%20find%20%E2%80%9Creconciliation%E2%80%9D%20in%20Myanmar.%20The%20initiative%20has%20not%20found%20support%20from%20ASEAN%E2%80%99s%20maritime%20members%2C%20including%20chair%20Indonesia%2C%20who%20see%20it%20as%20a%20move%20to%20legitimise%20the%20junta.%20Representatives%20from%20the%20Myanmar%20government-funded%20Myanmar%20Institute%20of%20Strategic%20and%20International%20Studies%20participated%20in%20the%20event.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20Biden-Modi%20joint%20statement%20of%20June%2022%20during%20the%20Indian%20prime%20minister%E2%80%99s%20US%20visit%2C%20the%20two%20leaders%20%E2%80%9Cexpressed%20deep%20concern%20about%20the%20deteriorating%20situation%20in%20Myanmar%2C%20and%20called%20for%20the%20release%20of%20all%20those%20arbitrarily%20detained%2C%20the%20establishment%20of%20constructive%20dialogue%2C%20and%20the%20transition%20of%20Myanmar%20toward%20an%20inclusive%20federal%20democratic%20system.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EResponding%20to%20a%20query%20about%20the%20India%20visit%20of%20Myint%20Kyaing%2C%20a%20spokesperson%20for%20the%20US%20embassy%20in%20New%20Delhi%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9CWe%20cannot%20comment%20on%20private%20diplomatic%20discussions.%20But%2C%20as%20Secretary%20of%20State%20Antony%20Blinken%20has%20said%2C%20%E2%80%98The%20United%20States%20will%20continue%20to%20work%20with%20a%20broad%20coalition%20of%20international%20partners%20to%20promote%20a