e%20to%20launch%20a%20SEAL%20Delivery%20Vehicle%20from%20the%20submarine%20USS%20Philadelphia%20in%20the%20Atlantic%20Ocean%20in%20May%202005.%3Cp%3EUS%20Navy%2FChief%20Photographer's%20Mate%20Andrew%20McKaskle%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20battery-powered%20Dry%20Combat%20Submersible%20is%20about%2040%20feet%20long%20and%20weighs%20a%20little%20over%2028%20tons.%20It%20is%20slightly%20larger%20than%20the%20SEAL%20Delivery%20Vehicles%20currently%20in%20use%20and%20won't%20be%20able%20to%20fit%20in%20the%20dry%20deck%20chambers%20that%20can%20be%20attached%20to%20the%20hull%20of%20a%20Navy%20submarine.%20It%20will%20instead%20have%20to%20be%20launched%20and%20recovered%20by%20a%20surface%20vessel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20perhaps%20the%20biggest%20difference%20is%20that%20the%20Dry%20Combat%20Submersible%20keeps%20frogmen%20dry%2C%20unlike%20the%20SEALs'%20other%20submersibles%2C%20which%20are%20open%20to%20the%20sea.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20DCS%20model%20designed%20for%20SOCOM%20by%20Lockheed%20Martin%20and%20its%20partners%20can%20carry%2010%20personnel%20%E2%80%94%20two%20crew%20and%20eight%20passengers%20%E2%80%94%20and%20has%20a%20maximum%20operating%20depth%20of%20nearly%20200%20feet%20as%20well%20as%20a%20range%20of%20nearly%20140%20miles%20when%20sailing%20at%205%20knots%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.hisutton.com%2FDry_Combat_Submersible.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enaval%20analyst%20H%20I%20Sutton%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Dry%20Combat%20Submersible%20has%20the%20potential%20to%20transform%20undersea%20warfare%20for%20special%20operators%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Gregg%20Bauer%2C%20a%20vice%20president%20at%20Lockheed%20Martin%2C%20which%20received%20the%20contract%20to%20develop%20DCS%20in%202016.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221028%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Navy%20Ohio-class%20guided-missile%20submarine%20USS%20Georgia%20seal%20delivery%20vehicle%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F62b33a5f5bcf7200181eb33b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22771%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUS%20Navy%20guided-missile%20sub%20USS%20Georgia%20leaves%20Naples%2C%20Italy%20carrying%20a%20dry%20deck%20chamber%20in%20August%202009.%3Cp%3EUS%20NavyMCS1%20John%20Parker%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDCS%20provides%20safe%2C%20clandestine%20delivery%20for%20occupants%20over%20long%20distances%20in%20a%20completely%20dry%20environment%20and%20features%20a%20lock-in%20and%20lock-out%20chamber%2C%26quot%3B%20Bauer%20said%20in%20a%20press%20release.%20%26quot%3BOccupants%20arrive%20at%20the%20mission%20warm%2C%20rested%2C%20hydrated%20and%20ready%2C%20making%20this%20vessel%20a%20key%20advantage%20in%20mission%20success.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lock-in%2Flock-out%20chamber%20allows%20operators%20to%20enter%20and%20exit%20while%20the%20submersible%20is%20submerged%2C%20Lockheed%20says%2C%20though%20the%20maximum%20depth%20for%20its%20use%20is%20just%20under%20100%20feet%2C%20according%20to%20Sutton.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20SOCOM's%20declaration%20moves%20the%20DCS%20closer%20to%20full%20fielding%2C%20the%20Pentagon's%20chief%20weapons%20tester%20said%20its%20report%20for%20fiscal%20year%202022%2C%20published%20in%20January%2C%20that%20SOCOM%20had%20%26quot%3Bdelayed%20the%20at-sea%20portion%20of%20operational%20test%26quot%3B%20until%20this%20fiscal%20year%20due%20to%20Covid-19%2C%20weather%20conditions%2C%20and%20%26quot%3Bmateriel%20issues%26quot%3B%20on%20the%20first%20DCS.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20said%20the%20testing%20office%20would%20share%20its%20assessment%20of%20DCS%20operational%20testing%20after%20the%20current%20fiscal%20year%2C%20which%20ends%20in%20September.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EUndersea%20armada%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Navy%20SEAL%20Delivery%20Vehicle%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F61410fdb2db0850019a97816%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221429%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20SEAL%20Delivery%20Vehicle%20is%20loaded%20onto%20the%20submarine%20USS%20Dallas%20in%20Norfolk%20in%20February%202006.%3Cp%3EUS%20Navy%2FChief%20Journalist%20Dave%20Fliesen%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EUS%20special-operations%20leaders%20have%20big%20ambitions%20for%20the%20Dry%20Combat%20Submersible%20and%20their%20other%20mini-subs.%20At%20a%20conference%20last%20year%2C%20the%20program%20manager%20for%20special-operations%20undersea%20systems%20at%20SOCOM%20said%20the%20DCS%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.navytimes.com%2Fnews%2Fyour-navy%2F2022%2F05%2F26%2Fnavy-seals-are-itching-for-upgrades-to-their-silent-underwater-rides%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eis%20like%20an%20electric%20truck%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20and%20would%20need%20to%20be%20capable%20of%20different%20roles%20and%20missions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20Navy%20and%20Naval%20Special%20Warfare%20Command%20have%20also%20been%20designing%20the%20Mark%2011%20Shallow%20Water%20Combat%20Submersible%2C%20which%20will%20replace%20the%20venerable%20Mark%208%20SEAL%20Delivery%20Vehicle%20that%20has%20been%20in%20use%20since%20the%201980s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Mark%2011%20is%20meant%20to%20carry%20small%20teams%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.19fortyfive.com%2F2023%2F05%2Fthe-u-s-navy-seals-seem-unstoppable-for-a-reason%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENavy%20SEALs%3C%2Fa%3E%20into%20an%20enemy%20harbors%20and%20shores%20without%20detection.%20It%20is%2023%20feet%20long%20and%20can%20hold%20six%20frogmen%20%E2%80%94%20two%20pilots%20and%20four%20combat%20divers%20%E2%80%94%20and%20is%20expected%20to%20reach%20full%20operational%20capability%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.navytimes.com%2Fnews%2Fyour-navy%2F2022%2F05%2F26%2Fnavy-seals-are-itching-for-upgrades-to-their-silent-underwater-rides%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ein%202027%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Mark%2011%20has%20a%20greater%20operational%20range%2C%20advanced%20sensors%2C%20a%20better%20navigation%20system%2C%20as%20well%20as%20a%20modular%20command-and-control%20structure%20that%20will%20allow%20the%20Navy%20to%20easily%20incorporate%20new%20technology.%20New%20tech%20and%20engineering%20will%20also%20allow%20the%20Mark%2011%20to%20operate%20at%20depths%20of%20about%20165%20feet.%20Its%20crew%20and%20passengers%20will%20also%20have%20to%20wear%20dry%20suits%20and%20oxygen%20tanks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221776%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Naval%20Special%20Warfare%20Navy%20SEAL%20Delivery%20Vehicle%20Mark%2011%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F62b3365ec38f470019c6bf8e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221332%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENaval%20Special%20Warfare%20operators%20train%20aboard%20a%20SEAL%20Delivery%20Vehicle%20Mark%2011%20at%20Pearl%20Harbor%20in%20May%202020.%3Cp%3EUS%20Navy%2FChief%20Mass%20Comm%20Specialist%20Christopher%20Perez%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20British%20military%20is%20already%20seeking%20Mark%2011s%20to%20replace%20the%20SDVs%20used%20by%20the%20Special%20Boat%20Service%2C%20the%20British%20counterpart%20to%20the%20SEALs.%20The%20US%20State%20Department%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dsca.mil%2Fpress-media%2Fmajor-arms-sales%2Funited-kingdom-seal-delivery-vehicle-sdv-mk-11-shallow-water-combat%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eapproved%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20sale%20of%20three%20Mark%2011s%20to%20the%20UK%20in%20September%202018.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Mark%208%20could%20deploy%20from%20a%20dry%20deck%20chamber%20on%20a%20submarine%20or%20be%20launched%20from%20a%20surface%20ship%20or%20an%20aircraft.%20Naval%20Special%20Warfare%20Command%20likely%20wanted%20to%20retain