ruth-carole-baskin-big-cat-rescue-2020-4%5C%22%3EBig%20cats%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%20like%20lions%2C%20tigers%20and%20pumas%20%E2%80%93%20are%20the%20attention-grabbing%20celebrities%20of%20the%20feline%20world.%20But%20of%20the%2041%20species%20of%20wild%20felines%2C%20the%20vast%20majority%20are%20about%20the%20size%20of%20a%20house%20cat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFew%20people%20have%20heard%20of%20the%20black-footed%20cat%20or%20the%20Borneo%20bay%20cat%2C%20much%20less%20the%20kodkod%2C%20oncilla%20or%20marbled%20cat.%20Clearly%2C%20the%20little-cat%20side%20of%20the%20feline%20family%20needs%20a%20better%20PR%20agent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20theory%2C%20any%20of%20these%20species%20could%20have%20been%20the%20progenitor%20of%20the%20domestic%20cat%2C%20but%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1126%2Fscience.1139518%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecent%20DNA%20studies%20demonstrate%20unequivocally%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0that%20today's%20house%20cats%20arose%20from%20the%20African%20wildcat%20%E2%80%93%20specifically%2C%20the%20North%20African%20subspecies%2C%C2%A0%3Cem%3EFelis%20silvestris%20lybica%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGiven%20the%20profusion%20of%20little%20pusses%2C%20why%20was%20the%20North%20African%20wildcat%20the%20one%20to%20give%20rise%20to%20our%20household%20companions%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20short%2C%20it%20was%20the%20right%20species%20in%20the%20right%20place%20at%20the%20right%20time.%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fancient-civilizations-that-were-hiding-in-plain-sight-2023-1%5C%22%3ECivilization%20began%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0in%20the%C2%A0Fertile%20Crescent%C2%A0about%2010%2C000%20years%20ago%2C%20when%20people%20first%20settled%20into%20villages%20and%20started%20growing%20food.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20area%20%E2%80%93%20spanning%20parts%20of%20modern-day%20Egypt%2C%20Turkey%2C%20Syria%2C%20Iran%20and%20more%20%E2%80%93%20is%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.wikipedia.org%2Fwiki%2FList_of_felids%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehome%20to%20numerous%20small%20cats%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20including%20the%20caracal%2C%20serval%2C%20jungle%20cat%20and%20sand%20cat.%20But%20of%20these%2C%20the%20African%20wildcat%20is%20the%20one%20that%20to%20this%20day%20enters%20villages%20and%C2%A0can%20be%20found%20around%20humans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfrican%20wildcats%20are%20among%20the%20friendliest%20of%20feline%20species%3B%20raised%20gently%2C%20they%C2%A0can%20make%20affectionate%20companions.%20In%20contrast%2C%20despite%20the%20most%20tender%20attention%2C%20their%20close%20relative%20the%20European%20wildcat%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hachettebookgroup.com%2Ftitles%2Fjohn-bradshaw%2Fcat-sense%2F9780465064960%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egrows%20up%20to%20be%20hellaciously%20mean%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGiven%20these%20tendencies%2C%20it's%20easy%20to%20envision%20what%20likely%20happened.%20People%20settled%20down%20and%20started%20raising%20crops%2C%20storing%20the%20excess%20for%20lean%20times.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20granaries%20led%20to%20rodent%20population%20explosions.%20Some%20African%20wildcats%20%E2%80%93%20those%20with%20the%20least%20fear%20of%20humans%20%E2%80%93%20took%20advantage%20of%20this%20bounty%20and%20started%20hanging%20around.%20People%20saw%20the%20benefit%20of%20their%20presence%20and%20treated%20the%20cats%20kindly%2C%20perhaps%20giving%20them%20shelter%20or%20food.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20boldest%20cats%20entered%20huts%20and%20perhaps%20allowed%20themselves%20to%20be%20petted%20%E2%80%93%20kittens%20are%20adorable!%20%E2%80%93%20and%2C%20voil%C3%A0%2C%20the%20domestic%20cat%20was%20born.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhere%20exactly%20domestication%20occurred%20%E2%80%93%20if%20it%20was%20a%20single%20place%20and%20not%20simultaneously%20throughout%20the%20entire%20region%20%E2%80%93%20is%20unclear.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhunting-scene-cave-painting-is-oldest-story-in-pictures-2019-12%5C%22%3Etomb%20paintings%20and%20sculptures%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0show%20that%20by%203%2C500%20years%20ago%2C%20domestic%20cats%20lived%20in%20Egypt.%C2%A0Genetic%20analysis%C2%A0%E2%80%93%20including%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1038%2Fs41559-017-0139%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDNA%20from%20Egyptian%20cat%20mummies%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%E2%80%93%20and%20archaeological%20data%20chart%20the%20feline%20diaspora.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20moved%20northward%20through%20Europe%20(and%20ultimately%20to%20North%20America)%2C%20south%20deeper%20into%20Africa%20and%20eastward%20to%20Asia.%20Ancient%20DNA%20even%20demonstrates%20that%C2%A0Vikings%20played%20a%20role%20in%20spreading%20felines%C2%A0far%20and%20wide.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20black%20and%20white%20cat%20that%20has%20recently%20vomited.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F63d82dba07f0aa0019008c36%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222268%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDaisy%2C%20the%20vomiting%20cat%20in%20question%3Cp%3ESophie%20Kleeman%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3EWhat%20cat%20traits%20did%20domestication%20emphasize%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDomestic%20cats%20possess%20many%20colors%2C%20patterns%20and%20hair%20textures%20not%20seen%20in%20wildcats.%20Some%C2%A0cat%20breeds%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fmost-beautiful-cat-breeds-2018-5%5C%22%3Edistinctive%20physical%20features%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20like%C2%A0munchkins'%20short%20legs%2C%C2%A0Siameses'%20elongated%20faces%C2%A0or%C2%A0Persians'%20lack%20of%20muzzle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%20many%20domestics%20appear%20basically%20indistinguishable%20from%20wildcats.%20In%20fact%2C%20only%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1073%2Fpnas.1410083111%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E13%20genes%20have%20been%20changed%20by%20natural%20selection%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0during%20the%20domestication%20process.%20By%20contrast%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fvideo-golden-retriever-convention-inverness-tweedmouth-scotland-highlands-2023-7%5C%22%3Ealmost%20three%20times%20as%20many%20genes%20changed%3C%2Fa%3E%20during%20the%20descent%20of%20dogs%20from%20wolves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20only%20two%20ways%20to%20indisputably%20identify%20a%20wildcat.%20You%20can%20measure%20the%20size%20of%20its%20brain%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0housecats%2C%C2%A0like%20other%20domestic%20animals%2C%20have%20evolved%20reductions%20in%20the%20parts%20of%20the%20brain%20associated%20with%20aggression%2C%20fear%20and%20overall%20reactivity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOr%20you%20can%20measure%20the%20length%20of%20its%20intestines%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1111%2Fj.1439-0469.2009.00537.x%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elonger%20in%20domestic%20cats%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0to%20digest%20vegetable-based%20food%20provided%20by%20or%20scavenged%20from%20humans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20significant%20evolutionary%20changes%20during%20cat%20domestication%20involve%20their%20behavior.%20The%20common%20view%20that%20domestic%20cats%20are%20aloof%20loners%20couldn't%20be%20further%20from%20the%20truth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20lots%20of%20domestic%20cats%20live%20together%20%E2%80%93%20in%20places%20where%20humans%20provide%20copious%20amounts%20of%20food%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.researchgate.net%2Fpublication%2F266757891_Group-living_in_the_Domestic_Cat_Its_Sociobiology_and_Epidemiology%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethey%20form%20social%20groups%20very%20similar%20to%20lion%20prides%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Composed%20of%20related%20females%2C%20these%20cats%20are%20very%20friendly%20%E2%80%93%20grooming%2C%20playing%20with%20and%20lying%20on%20top%20of%20each%20other%2C%20nursing%20each%20other's%20kittens%2C%20even%20serving%20as%20midwives%20during%20birth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20signal%20friendly%20intentions%2C%C2%A0an%20approaching%20cat%20raises%20its%20tail%20straight%20up%2C%20a%20trait%20shared%20with%20lions%20and%20no%20other%20feline%20species.%20As%20anyone%20who%20has%20lived%20with%20a%20cat%20knows%2C%20they%20use%20this%20%26quot%3BI%20want%20to%20be%20friends%26quot%3B%20message%20toward%20people%20as%20well%2C%20indicating%20that%20they%20include%20us%20in%20their%20social%20circle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221690%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Image%20of%20a%20cat.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64d524b27e9149001aa41e8f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221268%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EImage%20of%20a%20cat.%3Cp%3EThomas%20Winz%2F%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3EEvolution%20of%20a%20master%20manipulator%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHousehold%20cats%20are%20quite%20vocal%20to%20their%20human%20companions%2C%20using%C2%A0different%20meows%20to%20communicate%20different%20messages.%20Unlike%20the%20tail-up%20display%2C%20however%2C%20this%20is%20not%20an%20example%20of%20their%20treating%20us%20as%20part%20of%20their%20clan.%20Quite%20the%20contrary%2C%C2%A0cats%20rarely%20meow%20to%20one%20another.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20sound%20of%20these%20meows%20has%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1037%2F0735-7036.118.3.287%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eevolved%20during%20domestication%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0to%20more%20effectively%20communicate%20with%20us.%20Listeners%20rate%20the%20wildcat's%20call%20as%20more%20urgent%20and%20demanding%20(%26quot%3BMee%E2%80%91O%E2%80%91O%E2%80%91O%E2%80%91O%E2%80%91O%E2%80%91W!%26quot%3B)%20compared%20with%20the%20domestic%20cat's%20more%20pleasing%20(%26quot%3BMEE%E2%80%91ow%26quot%3B).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScientists%20suggest%20that%20these%20shorter%2C%20higher-pitched%20sounds%20are%C2%A0more%20pleasing%20to%20our%20auditory%20system%2C%20perhaps%20because%20young%20humans%20have%20high-pitched%20voices%2C%20and%20domestic%20cats%20have%20evolved%20accordingly%20to%20curry%20human%20favor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECats%20similarly%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fguides%2Fpets%2Fwhy-do-cats-meow%5C%22%3Emanipulate%20people%20with%20their%20purrs%3C%2Fa%3E.%20When%20they%20want%20something%20%E2%80%93%20picture%20a%20cat%20rubbing%20against%20your%20legs%20in%20the%20kitchen%20while%20you%20open%20a%20can%20of%20wet%20food%20%E2%80%93%20they%20purr%20extra%20loudly.%20And%20this%20purr%20is%20not%20the%20agreeable%20thrumming%20of%20a%20content%20cat%2C%20but%20an%20insistent%20chainsaw%20br-rr-oom%20demanding%20attention.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScientists%20digitally%20compared%20the%20spectral%20qualities%20of%20the%C2%A0two%20types%20of%20purrs%C2%A0and%20discovered%20that%20the%20major%20difference%20is%20that%20the%20insistent%20purr%20includes%20a%20component%20very%20similar%20to%20the%20sound%20of%20a%20human%20baby%20crying.%20People%2C%20of%20course%2C%20are%C2%A0innately%20attuned%20to%20this%20sound%2C%20and%20cats%20have%20evolved%20to%20take%20advantage%20of%20this%20sensitivity%20to%20get%20our%20attention.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20that%20won't%20surprise%20anyone%20who's%20lived%20with%20a%20cat.%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hachettebookgroup.com%2Ftitles%2Fjohn-bradshaw%2Fthe-trainable-cat%2F9780465093717%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAlthough%20cats%20are%20very%20trainable%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%E2%80%93%20they're%20very%20food%20motivated%20%E2%80%93%20cats%20usually%20train%20us%20more%20than%20we%20train%20them.%20As%20the%20old%20saw%20goes%2C%20%26quot%3BDogs%20have%20owners%2C%20cats%20have%20staff.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EJonathan%20Losos%20is%20a%20William%20H.%20Danforth%20distinguishe